As Zimbabwe celebrates 41 years of independence on Sunday, the country has pardoned and started releasing over 3,000 prisoners under a presidential amnesty. #eNCA​ correspondent Pindai Dube has the details #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - As Zimbabwe celebrates 41 years of independence on Sunday, the country has pardoned and started releasing over 3,000 prisoners under a presidential amnesty. The release is to decongest the overcrowded prisons amid the coronavirus pandemic. Zimbabwe's prison population stands at over 20,000 but has a holding capacity of only 17,000. READ: WATCH | Teachers in Zimbabwe to protest low pay Prisons in the capital Harare have reported 173 COVID-19 infections and one death. Zimbabwe has over 37,000 cases and just over 1,500 deaths. Watch the video above for more on this story.